# MANUFACTURER:		AT&T
# PRODUCT:			3B1 "Unix PC"
#
# DEVICE:			Mitsubishi M5L2764K (2764 EPROM)
# 					datecodes 842602 (14C) and 841316 (15C)
# LABEL:			Paper label with part number only.
#
# PROGRAMMER USED:	Conitec GALEP-4, software version 1.19.65
# HOST SYSTEM:		IBM ThinkPad T42, Windows XP SP3
#
# IMAGED BY:		Philip Pemberton
# 					<philpem@philpem.me.uk>
# 					<http://www.philpem.me.uk>
# DATE/TIME:		2010-11-26 12:00
#
#
# FILE LIST:
# 	Filename			Format		Board Loc.	Part Number
# 	14C 72-00616.bin	Raw Binary	14C			72-00616
# 	14C 72-00616.hex	Intel Hex	14C			72-00616
# 	15C 72-00617.bin	Raw Binary	15C			72-00617
# 	15C 72-00617.hex	Intel Hex	15C			72-00617
#
# NOTES:
# 	This is the Boot ROM set for the AT&T 3B1 Unix PC. These two ROMs
# 	contain a small (~4Kbyte) bootstrap program, which sets up the 3B1
# 	hardware, runs a RAM test, then boots the 3B1 from disc.
#
# 	ROM 15C contains code for even locations.
# 	ROM 14C contains code for odd locations.
#
# 	ROMs were provided by Michael Lee, and were sourced from a later-revision
# 	3B1 motherboard.
#
